<div class="introbox">
  <h1>What is the Debate?</h1>
  <p>This debate focusses on whether diversifying U.K universities' reading list, is an effective method in helping to 
    decolonise the university institution and improve the university experience of BAME students. Those who have engaged in this
    debate so far have contrasting ideas on whether this is successful. Some argue that the diverse reading list is a neccesisity to
    the voices that studens learn from are not just from one group of people. However, others argue that, although there are benefits
    to a diverse reading list, this is not enough to fully decolonise these insitutions. In order, to fully rid higher Education
    Insituitions (HEI) of racism, teaching practise requires change too.</p>
</div>


<!--internal link to jumping in the page-->

